1
00:01:57,081 --> 00:02:02,215
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Mamo! Who's that girl?</i>
<i>And why do you keep</i>
<i>avoiding me!?</i>

2
00:02:02,248 --> 00:02:06,681
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>[sob] This can't be</i>
<i>happening. It's got to</i>
<i>be a dream, it has to be!</i>

3
00:02:06,715 --> 00:02:11,381
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Droid Akumooda! How dare you</i>
<i>turn a young girl's romantic</i>
<i>dreams into a nightmare!</i>

4
00:02:11,415 --> 00:02:16,348
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>I am Sailor Moon!</i>
<i>In the name of the</i>
<i>Moon, I'll punish you!</i>

5
00:02:17,829 --> 00:02:20,762
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>[reading]</i>
<i>"Then the handsome prince</i>
<i>arrived at the thorn castle.</i>

6
00:02:20,796 --> 00:02:24,296
<i>...where he found the</i>
<i>beautiful princess asleep</i>
<i>from a witch's evil spell."</i>

7
00:02:24,329 --> 00:02:28,062
So he gave the princess
a loving kiss, and she
awoke"

8
00:02:28,096 --> 00:02:29,396
How boring.

9
00:02:29,429 --> 00:02:32,796
What are you talking
about? That's the best
part of the story!

10
00:02:32,829 --> 00:02:35,229
I heard this
fairytale
before...

11
00:02:35,262 --> 00:02:39,129
Aw, I thought if I
read it, you'd like
to hear it again.

12
00:02:39,162 --> 00:02:45,629
"The princess had been
awakened by her true love,
and so together, lived
happily ever after."

13
00:02:45,662 --> 00:02:46,462
The end!

14
00:02:46,496 --> 00:02:48,662
Aw! How romantic!

15
00:02:48,696 --> 00:02:50,396
...Right, Chibi-Usa?

16
00:02:53,329 --> 00:02:55,496
Wha-!? C'mon, it's
not <i>that</i> boring..!

17
00:02:55,529 --> 00:02:58,296
Usagi..! Just let
her sleep, okay?

18
00:02:58,329 --> 00:03:04,796
Look at her... she's
probably thinking about her
poor mother who's being held
captive in the future.

19
00:03:04,829 --> 00:03:08,296
Yeah. I wish there was
some way we could help
her...

20
00:03:14,296 --> 00:03:18,696
"Awaken the Sleeping Beauty:
Mamoru's Distress"

21
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:26,262
[grunts]

22
00:03:31,062 --> 00:03:32,362
[grunt]

23
00:03:32,396 --> 00:03:37,229
Isn't it just wonderful
Mamo- at last we're
finally married!

24
00:03:37,262 --> 00:03:49,296
Wait... Usako...

25
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:54,696
Usako! Nooooo!

26
00:03:55,162 --> 00:03:58,196
[gasp]
[sobs]

27
00:03:58,229 --> 00:04:02,762
<i>(Voice)</i>
<i>Mamoru Chiba, you must stay</i>
<i>away from Usagi Tsukino.</i>

28
00:04:04,796 --> 00:04:09,062
So it's you again...
Tell me, who are you!?

29
00:04:09,096 --> 00:04:13,662
<i>(Voice)</i>
<i>The moment that the two</i>
<i>of you are wed, the world</i>
<i>will come to an end...</i>

30
00:04:13,696 --> 00:04:17,696
<i>(Voice)</i>
<i>...and tragedy will befall</i>
<i>Usagi Tsukino, Princess</i>
<i>Serenity!</i>

31
00:04:17,729 --> 00:04:19,062
[gasp]

32
00:04:19,096 --> 00:04:22,629
Grr... You expect me
to really believe that!?

33
00:04:22,662 --> 00:04:26,629
Is torturing me all
you want to do!? Stop
with these nightmares!

34
00:04:28,562 --> 00:04:32,196
<i>(Voice)</i>
<i>This is a truth</i>
<i>you cannot escape.</i>

35
00:04:32,829 --> 00:04:35,762
That's all a lie!
It can't be!

36
00:04:35,796 --> 00:04:37,462
No!

37
00:04:38,329 --> 00:04:44,196
[thinking]
So, if I go near her,
Usa will encounter
tragedy...

38
00:04:44,229 --> 00:04:46,496
But is that really
true!?

39
00:04:49,396 --> 00:04:51,229
Usako...

40
00:04:53,129 --> 00:04:54,262
[gasp]

41
00:04:55,729 --> 00:04:57,596
How did that
happen..?

42
00:04:58,162 --> 00:05:00,196
<i>(Voice)</i>
<i>Tragedy</i> will befall her.

43
00:05:01,262 --> 00:05:13,396
(Thinking)
So then, is it true..?
Must I stay away from
Usako, after all..?

44
00:05:13,429 --> 00:05:19,362
(Thinking)
Why...? Why should things
end up disastrous if Usako
and I love each other?

45
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:22,696
Hi Mamo...

46
00:05:22,729 --> 00:05:24,262
[gasp]

47
00:05:24,296 --> 00:05:28,162
I'm surprised seeing you
here this early in the
morning. Guess it must
be fate...

48
00:05:28,196 --> 00:05:33,329
Hey, by the way, has
Chibi-Usa said anything
to you about Crystal
Tokyo?

49
00:05:33,362 --> 00:05:35,096
No, she hasn't
told me anything.

50
00:05:36,462 --> 00:05:38,396
Hey, wait- Mamo!
Where are you going?

51
00:05:38,429 --> 00:05:41,162
I'm going for a morning
run to stay in shape.

52
00:05:42,162 --> 00:05:43,496
But, Mamo--

53
00:05:44,429 --> 00:05:47,229
(Thinking)
Forgive me, Usako...

54
00:05:47,829 --> 00:05:50,062
Mamo, I haven't given
up on you yet...

55
00:05:50,096 --> 00:05:54,396
Watch me! I'll do
whatever it takes to
win back your love!

56
00:05:54,429 --> 00:05:56,596
I swear...

57
00:05:57,529 --> 00:05:59,662
<i>...One day.</i>

58
00:06:04,462 --> 00:06:05,762
[thinking]
What should I do..?

59
00:06:07,529 --> 00:06:09,362
(Motoki)
Hey Mamoru,
what's up?

60
00:06:09,396 --> 00:06:11,562
Oh, Motoki...

61
00:06:11,596 --> 00:06:15,562
You've seemed kinda
down lately. So is
there something that's
been bothering you?

62
00:06:15,596 --> 00:06:18,029
No...

63
00:06:18,062 --> 00:06:21,162
Come on, we're best
friends! Tell me what's
going on with you-

64
00:06:21,196 --> 00:06:23,662
-I bet you'll feel
better if you talk
to me about it.

65
00:06:23,696 --> 00:06:25,396
Thank, I really
appreciate it.

66
00:06:25,429 --> 00:06:27,762
sluuuuuurp.

67
00:06:27,796 --> 00:06:32,262
Motoki, what do you
think is the best way
to get a girl not to
like you anymore?

68
00:06:32,296 --> 00:06:34,129
<i>[slap]</i>
Huh? Why would you
want to do that?

69
00:06:34,162 --> 00:06:39,596
I need help finding a
way to become the sort
of guy that girls end
up really hating...

70
00:06:39,629 --> 00:06:43,729
Here's your strawberry
sundae... Hey Mamoru!

71
00:06:48,462 --> 00:06:52,062
So Usagi, have you
had a chance to ask
Chibi-Usa anything?

72
00:06:52,096 --> 00:06:53,796
Nahh...

73
00:06:53,829 --> 00:06:57,129
Well, here's what we
know. Chibi-Usa is
from the future--

74
00:06:57,162 --> 00:07:01,396
--And her home, Crystal
Tokyo, is under attack
by this Black Moon Clan.

75
00:07:01,429 --> 00:07:05,696
And on top of that,
isn't Chibi-Usa's
mother being held
captive by that clan?

76
00:07:05,729 --> 00:07:07,396
Yeah...

77
00:07:07,429 --> 00:07:11,562
And now Crimson Rubeus
and the 4 Spectre Sisters
are here trying to
destroy our world...

78
00:07:11,596 --> 00:07:14,129
Usagi! Stop acting
like this doesn't
matter!

79
00:07:14,229 --> 00:07:15,696
Besides, your ice
cream's melting...

80
00:07:15,729 --> 00:07:20,796
So hey, I need your
advice. Why do you
think Mamo's avoiding
me?

81
00:07:20,829 --> 00:07:22,862
-What. -What.
-What. -What.

82
00:07:22,896 --> 00:07:27,529
Will you snap out of it!
Right now our top priority
is to find out exactly
where our enemy is hiding!

83
00:07:27,562 --> 00:07:30,662
We all need to get out
there and gather as
much info as we can.

84
00:07:30,696 --> 00:07:31,796
-Right! -Right!
-Right! -Right!

85
00:07:31,829 --> 00:07:34,162
[sigh]

86
00:07:38,696 --> 00:07:40,696
[vroom vroom]

87
00:07:40,729 --> 00:07:44,096
Stop revving that
motorcycle... Hey!
You! Knock it off!

88
00:07:45,462 --> 00:07:48,729
Mamo?

89
00:07:48,762 --> 00:07:50,329
Wait! Hold on!

90
00:07:52,262 --> 00:07:55,562
Mamo! Who's that girl
you're giving a ride?
Is she a relative?

91
00:07:55,596 --> 00:07:57,262
..Your cousin?
Or is she...

92
00:07:57,296 --> 00:08:01,762
It's none of your
business who she is,
and stop being so nosey
about my personal life!

93
00:08:02,629 --> 00:08:03,662
[gasp]

94
00:08:03,696 --> 00:08:05,596
Okay. You better
hold on tight.

95
00:08:05,696 --> 00:08:08,462
But Mamoru, who
is this girl?

96
00:08:08,729 --> 00:08:10,729
(Mamoru)
Eh, she's just
a friend...

97
00:08:21,129 --> 00:08:23,796
So I'm... "just
a friend..?"

98
00:08:23,829 --> 00:08:28,529
[crying]

99
00:08:38,329 --> 00:08:42,462
<i>[Thinking]</i>
<i>Usako... We must be</i>
<i>apart until I figure</i>
<i>out my nightmares...</i>

100
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:01,662
What's that noise?
Maybe it's a burglar.

101
00:09:05,696 --> 00:09:08,329
[small sob]

102
00:09:08,362 --> 00:09:10,562
Hey, Usagi,
what's wrong?

103
00:09:10,596 --> 00:09:13,229
[nom]

104
00:09:13,629 --> 00:09:16,462
You know, eating after
midnight gives you
indigestion and might
make you fat...

105
00:09:19,762 --> 00:09:26,629
[sob] Well I don't
care one bit! So
what if I get fat!?
[cries]

106
00:09:26,662 --> 00:09:29,496
My Mamo has got himself
a new girlfriend..!

107
00:09:29,529 --> 00:09:31,229
[gasp]

108
00:09:31,262 --> 00:09:35,162
Why should I even care
about what I eat, after
all, the man that I
love, now hates me...

109
00:09:35,196 --> 00:09:37,662
[crying]

110
00:09:37,696 --> 00:09:40,562
[small cry]

111
00:09:43,096 --> 00:09:47,196
<i>[Thinking]</i>
<i>Mamo... it can't be</i>
<i>true that you have</i>
<i>a girlfriend, can it?</i>

112
00:09:49,729 --> 00:09:50,796
[loud truck honks]

113
00:09:50,829 --> 00:09:51,762
[frightened cry]

114
00:09:52,196 --> 00:09:55,562
[screaming]

115
00:09:58,229 --> 00:10:00,496
[sluuurp] Huh?
What's that
bright light?

116
00:10:01,096 --> 00:10:04,796
Usagi! We have a big
problem. I can't find
Chibi-Usa anywhere in
the house!

117
00:10:04,829 --> 00:10:08,029
I just saw a flash
of light! Could it
be Chibi-Usa?

118
00:10:08,062 --> 00:10:11,329
You say you've
detected traces
of Rabbit's energy?

119
00:10:11,362 --> 00:10:14,196
Yes, sir. We think
she's somewhere
near Juban Park.

120
00:10:14,229 --> 00:10:16,729
Go! Find and
attack her at
once!

121
00:10:16,762 --> 00:10:20,362
[running breaths]

122
00:10:20,396 --> 00:10:24,096
There you are...
Now we've got you,
Rabbit.

123
00:10:24,129 --> 00:10:24,696
[gasp]

124
00:10:26,462 --> 00:10:28,696
Someone help me!

125
00:10:28,729 --> 00:10:29,396
Stop running!

126
00:10:29,429 --> 00:10:31,229
We're coming,
Chibi-Usa!

127
00:10:31,262 --> 00:10:32,996
Hurry! Help!

128
00:10:34,629 --> 00:10:37,396
You creeps are gonna
get it b ig time because
I'm in a really bad
mood tonight..!

129
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:40,529
Moon Crystal Power..!
Make Up!

130
00:10:55,562 --> 00:11:05,596
♪Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...♪

131
00:11:05,596 --> 00:11:19,696
♪Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...♪

132
00:11:23,762 --> 00:11:25,229
[cries]

133
00:11:25,262 --> 00:11:27,296
Heh, tonight's your
last night alive.

134
00:11:27,329 --> 00:11:29,096
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Not if I can</i>
<i>help it!</i>

135
00:11:29,129 --> 00:11:30,762
[gasps]

136
00:11:30,796 --> 00:11:33,329
-Sailor Moon.
-Sailor Moon.

137
00:11:33,362 --> 00:11:33,819
Ah!

138
00:11:33,852 --> 00:11:35,452
[hisses]

139
00:11:35,585 --> 00:11:37,419
[screaming]

140
00:11:37,852 --> 00:11:42,919
Two full grown women...
Ganging up to hurt a
little girl...!

141
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,819
I can't forgive you
for picking on her!

142
00:11:46,652 --> 00:11:53,385
I am Sailor Moon! And
now, in the name of the
Moon, I'll punish you.

143
00:11:54,352 --> 00:11:58,685
[chuckle]
Sailor Moon, we have
been waiting for you
to show up here...

144
00:11:58,719 --> 00:12:00,552
You've been
"waiting for me?"

145
00:12:00,585 --> 00:12:02,119
Akumooda! Come
down here!

146
00:12:05,185 --> 00:12:08,585
[melodic voice]
Dream dream dream...

147
00:12:08,619 --> 00:12:09,385
[gasp]

148
00:12:10,519 --> 00:12:13,119
Dream dream...!

149
00:12:21,852 --> 00:12:22,852
Sailor Moon!

150
00:12:22,885 --> 00:12:24,652
R!

151
00:12:37,561 --> 00:12:41,227
Sailor Moon R!

152
00:12:45,127 --> 00:12:48,627
[melodic voice]
Dream dream dream...

153
00:12:48,661 --> 00:12:50,161
Hey! Stop that!

154
00:12:50,194 --> 00:12:52,261
Sailor Moon! Be
careful..!

155
00:12:52,294 --> 00:12:56,161
Sleep, sleep, sleep,
sleep, sleep...

156
00:12:56,194 --> 00:12:57,494
[weak moan]

157
00:12:57,527 --> 00:12:59,827
Sailor Moon, you mustn't
fall asleep now..!

158
00:12:59,861 --> 00:13:04,994
I'm feeling really
stuffed from all those
late-night snacks I ate
earlier. Nighty-night!

159
00:13:05,761 --> 00:13:06,204
[frightened whimper]

160
00:13:07,437 --> 00:13:10,004
[giggle]
That was easy.

161
00:13:10,037 --> 00:13:12,637
Now for you...
Die, Rabbit.

162
00:13:12,671 --> 00:13:14,004
[whimper]

163
00:13:14,037 --> 00:13:14,971
[surprised gasps]

164
00:13:18,937 --> 00:13:22,404
I'm glad we decided
to stop by to check
that energy spike!

165
00:13:22,437 --> 00:13:24,204
Not you people
again!

166
00:13:24,237 --> 00:13:26,471
There's only two
of us, and there's
four of them!

167
00:13:26,504 --> 00:13:29,337
We're at a big
disadvantage here,
let's go!

168
00:13:30,304 --> 00:13:32,337
Uh, hey wait!

169
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:34,337
Hey! Are you afraid
to fight us!?

170
00:13:34,371 --> 00:13:39,571
Akumooda is more than
enough to handle you
little girls! [laugh]

171
00:13:39,604 --> 00:13:43,104
Akumooda, I want you
to do the same thing
you did to Sailor Moon.

172
00:13:43,137 --> 00:13:46,237
Lead them to nightmare
land and then you can
finish them off!

173
00:13:47,504 --> 00:13:50,537
[melodic voice]
Dream, dream, dream,
dream, dream...

174
00:13:50,571 --> 00:13:53,437
She's trying to
use hypnosis to
beat you!

175
00:13:53,471 --> 00:13:56,504
Whatever you do,
you can't let her
put you to sleep!

176
00:13:56,537 --> 00:14:03,304
Now go to sleep....
Sleep... Time to sleep.

177
00:14:03,471 --> 00:14:06,071
[grunts]

178
00:14:06,104 --> 00:14:09,571
We're not gonna
let you put us
to sleep..!

179
00:14:09,604 --> 00:14:15,904
Rin, Pyo, To, Sha,
Kai-Jin, Retsu-Zai-Zen!

180
00:14:15,937 --> 00:14:17,571
Evil Spirit be
exorcised!

181
00:14:17,604 --> 00:14:19,637
[death scream]

182
00:14:24,171 --> 00:14:26,904
Thanks, Mars. We were
almost overwhelmed by
that thing...

183
00:14:26,937 --> 00:14:27,386
Mhm!

184
00:14:29,186 --> 00:14:32,053
Sailor Moon!
Wake up!

185
00:14:32,086 --> 00:14:34,753
Sailor Moon will
continue to dream...

186
00:14:34,786 --> 00:14:40,319
...and as she dreams,
her energy will be
drained out of her
until she finally dies...

187
00:14:40,653 --> 00:14:42,253
[gasps]

188
00:14:43,053 --> 00:14:44,986
[groan]

189
00:14:45,019 --> 00:14:45,653
What just
happened!?

190
00:14:45,686 --> 00:14:47,453
[gasp] Sailor Moon!

191
00:14:47,719 --> 00:14:49,453
Sailor Moon!

192
00:14:49,486 --> 00:14:51,353
Sailor Moon!

193
00:14:51,386 --> 00:14:52,986
Please, wake up!

194
00:14:53,019 --> 00:14:55,086
C'mon, Sailor Moon!
Say something!

195
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:03,186
[running gasps]

196
00:15:06,253 --> 00:15:10,153
Mamo! It's me!
I'm-- whoa!
...Mamo!

197
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:13,086
Sailor Moon!
Please wake up!

198
00:15:13,119 --> 00:15:14,119
Sailor Moon!

199
00:15:14,153 --> 00:15:15,653
You have to
snap out of it!

200
00:15:17,219 --> 00:15:19,586
You can see the
energy's draining
from her body!

201
00:15:19,619 --> 00:15:22,653
If we can't wake her
up, then Sailor Moon
will end up dead..!

202
00:15:23,519 --> 00:15:25,719
What can we do!?

203
00:15:25,753 --> 00:15:28,986
You have to wake
up! Come on! [sobs]

204
00:15:31,653 --> 00:15:34,353
Mamo..!

205
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:40,519
Please don't
leave me!!

206
00:15:41,219 --> 00:15:43,053
Wake up!

207
00:15:43,753 --> 00:15:46,453
Ma...mo... Don't
go....

208
00:15:50,119 --> 00:15:51,086
[gasp]

209
00:15:51,119 --> 00:15:52,719
We're running out
of time!

210
00:15:52,753 --> 00:15:55,153
She'll die if we
can't help her!

211
00:15:55,186 --> 00:15:56,986
Huh?

212
00:15:57,019 --> 00:16:01,586
Why should I even care
about what I eat? After
all, the man that I
love, now hates me...

213
00:16:04,119 --> 00:16:06,553
Luna, wait! Where
are you going!?

214
00:16:12,386 --> 00:16:14,086
Ah! What the--?

215
00:16:14,286 --> 00:16:16,753
Mamoru! Sailor Moon's
in really big trouble!

216
00:16:16,786 --> 00:16:20,153
Please! You just have
to come with me to
help save her life!

217
00:16:20,553 --> 00:16:22,386
We've got to hurry!

218
00:16:22,419 --> 00:16:25,553
<i>You see, she's in</i>
<i>this deep, deadly sleep</i>
<i>and you're the only one</i>
<i>who can wake her up..!</i>

219
00:16:25,586 --> 00:16:27,619
<i>Only you can</i>
<i>save her..!</i>

220
00:16:28,186 --> 00:16:30,019
I'm not sure that
I can help...

221
00:16:30,053 --> 00:16:36,019
But weren't you and Sailor
Moon in love with one
another in a world in
the distant past?!

222
00:16:36,053 --> 00:16:39,586
Why are you suddenly
acting so cold to her?

223
00:16:42,419 --> 00:16:44,653
I have to...

224
00:16:50,486 --> 00:16:53,086
If you don't help,
Sailor Moon will die!

225
00:16:59,586 --> 00:17:04,053
<i>Sailor Moon...</i>
<i>Usako... Just hang</i>
<i>on 'til I get there.</i>

226
00:17:08,086 --> 00:17:11,219
I won't let you
die, Usako!

227
00:17:13,786 --> 00:17:18,219
[out of breath]

228
00:17:18,786 --> 00:17:22,253
Mamo... wait!

229
00:17:23,286 --> 00:17:26,019
Sailor Moon! You've
got to wake up..!

230
00:17:26,586 --> 00:17:28,419
Can you even
hear us!?

231
00:17:29,053 --> 00:17:32,153
Oh, Sailor Moon!
Please wake up!

232
00:17:32,486 --> 00:17:34,486
We've got to think
of something to do
here...

233
00:17:35,719 --> 00:17:37,753
Come out of
your sleep...

234
00:17:37,786 --> 00:17:40,053
Hey body temperature
is getting lower...!

235
00:17:40,086 --> 00:17:40,686
What?!

236
00:17:45,786 --> 00:17:48,219
Look over there-
It's Tuxedo Mask.

237
00:17:49,186 --> 00:17:53,253
She's right, it <i>is</i>
Tuxedo Mask... Is
he here to help?

238
00:17:56,519 --> 00:17:59,086
[gasp]

239
00:17:59,119 --> 00:17:59,586
Oh no!

240
00:18:00,453 --> 00:18:05,053
Sailor Moon! Wake up!
Sailor Moon..!

241
00:18:09,653 --> 00:18:10,719
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Mamo...</i>

242
00:18:10,753 --> 00:18:12,086
[gasp]

243
00:18:15,386 --> 00:18:19,186
Usako... Please
forgive me...

244
00:18:28,186 --> 00:18:30,586
Stop that...!

245
00:18:46,286 --> 00:18:50,019
The power of love
woke Sailor Moon and
restored her energy!

246
00:18:51,619 --> 00:18:54,619
Mamo... You're
so warm...

247
00:18:54,653 --> 00:18:59,253
Sailor Moon...
Thank goodness.

248
00:19:05,619 --> 00:19:08,253
I don't believe it.
It's just like that
fairy tale...

249
00:19:11,253 --> 00:19:16,353
How dare you
interfere Tuxedo
Mask..!

250
00:19:16,386 --> 00:19:17,453
Grrrrr!

251
00:19:17,486 --> 00:19:19,119
Look out!

252
00:19:19,153 --> 00:19:20,986
[screaming]

253
00:19:21,019 --> 00:19:23,219
[grunt]

254
00:19:23,253 --> 00:19:27,753
A girl is always supposed
to dream of doing whatever it
takes to help her win the
heart of the boy she loves!

255
00:19:27,786 --> 00:19:31,253
Sailor Moon...
Nightmares for you!

256
00:19:31,286 --> 00:19:33,353
I can't forgive you
for what you've done.

257
00:19:49,186 --> 00:19:53,686
♪Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...
Sailor Moon...♪

258
00:19:53,719 --> 00:20:00,119
Moon Princess...
Halation...!

259
00:20:03,486 --> 00:20:07,719
[death scream]

260
00:20:14,419 --> 00:20:19,419
Sailor Moon, as always,
your finishing technique
is breathtaking...

261
00:20:19,453 --> 00:20:22,986
Tuxedo Mask, do you
have feelings for
me after all?

262
00:20:23,019 --> 00:20:25,219
Sailor Moon...

263
00:20:26,253 --> 00:20:29,119
[grunt] No, I don't! I
really don't love you!

264
00:20:29,653 --> 00:20:33,719
[gasp] But how can
that be? You literally
just saved my life...

265
00:20:34,553 --> 00:20:37,419
Those are different
things... Very different!

266
00:20:38,653 --> 00:20:40,019
[gasp]

267
00:20:41,686 --> 00:20:44,953
The red strong of fate
that tied the two of us
together has now been
cut to pieces...

268
00:20:50,319 --> 00:20:52,319
Noooooo!!!

269
00:21:03,286 --> 00:21:07,319
[gasp]

270
00:21:08,319 --> 00:21:11,119
Tuxedo Mask!
Whyyyy!?

271
00:21:14,353 --> 00:21:21,119
Sailor Moon...
Please forgive
me, Usako...

272
00:21:31,219 --> 00:21:33,286
What!? Wait. <i>You're</i>
Unazuki!? So...

273
00:21:33,319 --> 00:21:36,686
Then that means,
you're Motoki's
younger sister?

274
00:21:36,786 --> 00:21:41,553
That's right. Mamoru
did me a huge favor
yesterday by giving me
a ride on his bike...

275
00:21:41,586 --> 00:21:43,353
So that was you
on his bike with
him..?

276
00:21:43,386 --> 00:21:48,419
Yeah! I got so busy
here at work that I was
going to be late for my
date with my boyfriend!

277
00:21:48,453 --> 00:21:49,386
So he helped me out.

278
00:21:49,419 --> 00:21:52,419
So Mamoru isn't in
any way your boyfriend?

279
00:21:52,453 --> 00:21:59,186
Don't be silly! I've got
my own great boyfriend
that I love very, very
much! See ya!

280
00:22:00,353 --> 00:22:05,319
Yes! That's great
news! She's already
got a boyfriend!

281
00:22:07,786 --> 00:22:14,186
Okay...but then, why's
Mamo avoiding me and why
does he keep lying to me?
I don't get it!

282
00:22:16,586 --> 00:22:18,919
Well, there's one
thing I know for sure.

283
00:22:18,953 --> 00:22:24,619
I'll figure everything out and
then I'll win back his love and
we'll live happily ever after
exactly like I want us to!

284
00:22:29,019 --> 00:22:31,219
Oh yeah!!

285
00:24:10,486 --> 00:24:14,319
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Hey, Rei, who's that lady?</i>
<i>Isn't she a salesperson</i>
<i>for cosmetics..?</i>

286
00:24:14,353 --> 00:24:17,386
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>No, she's Koan, one</i>
<i>of the four Spectre</i>
<i>Sisters!</i>

287
00:24:17,419 --> 00:24:20,353
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Oh no! Not her again!</i>
<i>SHe sure is persistent!</i>

288
00:24:20,386 --> 00:24:25,719
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>Wake up Koan! What you see as</i>
love is wrong! You're confused,
<i>that's not what true love is!</i>

289
00:24:25,753 --> 00:24:26,653
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Rei! Look out!</i>

290
00:24:26,686 --> 00:24:28,486
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>Koan!</i>

291
00:24:28,519 --> 00:24:32,686
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Next time on Sailor Moon R:</i>
<i>"Battle of the Flames of Love!</i>
<i>Mars vs. Koan"</i>

292
00:24:32,719 --> 00:24:36,053
<i>The moonlight is a</i>
<i>messenger of love.</i>

